  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - DRUID</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>30-33 QUICKLY IN THE OVERTHERE</font> - <small>Sundrop Moonrise, Bertoxxulous</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>To begin with, here are my stats from level 30-33 (time of this writing).  The stats and race comparison should be a good basis for judging whether this is a good strategy for you.<br>
<br>
30-33 Halfling Druid – with 170-176 wisdom and agility of 103.  (I believe anyone with wisdom over 150 could have success with this method)<br>
<Br>
I will start by saying that this saying that I love this zone.  It is  8000 x 8000 and is perfect for kiting.  This strategy will not work if you are below lvl 30 or if you have not trained 1 point into each of your specialization skills (especially evocation).  Otherwise read on for the best experience(nearly risk free and no faction hits) that I have found. <br>
<Br>
For the early 30s, you have 3 enemies to track down and kill.  STONELEER cockatrices, Sarnak BERZERKERS, and THORNY Succulants.  You might want to grab a pen and jot those names down, so you don't do like I did:  realize you made a kiting mistake when you get to 20% mana left and the mob has 40% health...  Those enemies listed above are lvl 29-33 and have 1131-1231 hit points.   You can target and kill any of these regardless of whether they are blue or red and they all give great exp.  However, blues seem to give me better experience in the same amount of play time because they resist or partial resist a LOT less.<br>
<br>
First off, throw out your lvl 1 snare spell and use the level 29 ENSNARE.  It lasts about 9 minutes and will keep you a safe distance away from the mobs.  Simply ensnare, nuke, run, nuke, run, nuke until the mob is about 20% health (trying to run away and thus stopped and scared because of ensnare).  Then cast your damage over time (preferably creeping crud because it is rarely resisted) and med up while the creature dies.  The results: you can normally be back to 50-60% mana when your dot'd mob dies.  <br>
<Br>
<BR>
Warnings and Reccommendations:<br>
<br>
*Get a CLARITY!  Be the best friend of any enchanters you ever see in this zone.  Be nice and offer donations and/or SoW for a clarity.  You want to keep them happy because you will want to come back every 30 or so minutes for another! (Enchanters and clarity rock :)   )<br>
<br>
*Never attempt to kite any kunark rhinos or any of the sabretooth tiger series of mobs.  They run about 95% as fast as you do with Spirit of Wolf or Wolf form.  Wolf form will not keep you from being Killed on Site to these creatures.  So I use SoW (since i rarely attack anyways).  SoW will not leave you if you have to zone.<br>
<br>
*I have found that the best area to kite is in the southwestern corner near the Skyfire Mountain Entrance (loc is -1000, +3800).  I typically kite along the zone wall between the Skyfire entrance and the southwest corner.  Do not attempt to kite near the Frontier Mountain zone for 3 reasons:<br>
1.  This part of the zone is usually overcrowded and you will have your mob (who will be at about        60% health) kill stolen from you.  I had it happen three times before I went to skyfire side... <br>
2.  It is a long run down the corridor to zone to Frontier Mtns. <br>
3.  Each and every night(everquest time) the Dragoon guards (level 50 or so) will get trained through this area and all non-evil races will be killed on site.<br>
<br>
*Most mobs drop 1-4pp, so you will not be getting rich.  However, I listened to the shouts and out of characters and /tell those people who needed a port.  You can port people for 20pp about 95% of the time.  However, if a lower level character comes in on the boat and realizes he/she is KOS to the town in the Northwest please port them too.  It is horrible to be lost AND scared for your life.<br>
<br>
Final Thoughts:<br>
<br>
1. I know that direct damage kiting is not always the most "mana efficient" method of killing a mob.  However, the halfling race has a base charisma of 50 and animal charms do not last long!<br>
<br>
2.  I love this method of kiting because it allows me to do other things such as homework for 3-4 minutes while I meditate.  <br>
<br>
3.  While meditating in between kills, you will want to sit up on the zone wall and away from entrances to other zones (because of the occasional train).  So make sure you pull your mob where you want to med while you kite.  I normally pull right up to the zone wall and cast the DOT and sit right next to my little experience friend!<br>
<br>
4.  After you reach level 34 and get lightning strike you will want to quad kite these same enemies for mondo experience.  However, I am not yet 34 and have never quad kited.  Although I have watched many druids do it here and they all LOVE it. :) So if your level 34 and above you may want to combine this strategy guide with one of those quad kiting guides.<br>
<br>
I wish all of you druids good luck and I hope you find this strategy as useful as I did (3 levels in 3 days).<br>
</p></td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
